Troop[122].pages[1].command[3].textData: "The only place where I can truly be free, are my dreams."
Troop[122].pages[1].command[6].textData: "In the vast open plains of this netherworld, I hold no burden
Troop[122].pages[1].command[7].textData: over the worries of my past life."
Troop[122].pages[1].command[10].textData: "Of course this is a flawed logic..."
Troop[122].pages[1].command[13].textData: "One should not bind oneself to a set location, one should
Troop[122].pages[1].command[14].textData: be able to wander the world like a wind."
Troop[122].pages[1].command[17].textData: "But even gods are allowed to have flaws, no?"
Troop[122].pages[2].command[1].textData: As time will pass, will you tell people about your monumental
Troop[122].pages[2].command[4].textData: How you passed through all the hardships the dungeons laid
Troop[122].pages[2].command[5].textData: before you and about you eventual ascension?
Troop[122].pages[2].command[9].textData: Stories about your fabled endeavours are passed to people
Troop[122].pages[2].command[10].textData: of all ages. Your tales inspire many in the times to come
Troop[122].pages[2].command[16].textData: Your story is left unspoken and unsung. There are rumours here
Troop[122].pages[2].command[17].textData: and there but for the most part, the era of the new gods
Troop[122].pages[2].command[22].textData: In the coming era, mankind is at the brink of chaos. Diseases
Troop[122].pages[2].command[23].textData: run wild and kingdoms wage war with hundreds of thousands
Troop[122].pages[2].command[24].textData: of casualties on all fronts, both women and children included.
Troop[122].pages[2].command[26].textData: You would have the power to interrupt and potentially stop
Troop[122].pages[2].command[27].textData: this. You have the strength to stop the mindless killing.
Troop[122].pages[2].command[28].textData: But that would require you to step out of the plain of this
Troop[122].pages[2].command[31].textData: Instead, you could try to affect mankind through religion
Troop[122].pages[2].command[32].textData: and beliefs. Affecting the whole culture means slow change
Troop[122].pages[2].command[33].textData: and its effects don't save those in immediate peril, but
Troop[122].pages[2].command[34].textData: religion might have more long-lasting effects.
Troop[122].pages[2].command[35].textChoi: Save the mankind with your strength
Troop[122].pages[2].command[38].textData: You leave your golden throne to disrupt the ongoing wars.
Troop[122].pages[2].command[39].textData: With overwhelming strength you crush entire armies that stand
Troop[122].pages[2].command[40].textData: in your way. Kings and sultans of the time are left in terror
Troop[122].pages[2].command[43].textData: Once you are done with your rage, mankind is left in a
Troop[122].pages[2].command[44].textData: state of chaos. Common people got no one to turn onto and
Troop[122].pages[2].command[45].textData: thus they seek safety from smaller tribes and communes.
Troop[122].pages[2].command[47].textData: By meddling with the mankind, you ended up halting the
Troop[122].pages[2].command[48].textData: technological and cultural progress. People are also less
Troop[122].pages[2].command[49].textData: self-imposed because of relying on gods in the past.
Troop[122].pages[2].command[51].textData: The civilizations are back to iron age-like structure where
Troop[122].pages[2].command[52].textData: physical strength is the only thing that matters.
Troop[122].pages[2].command[55].textData: You watch other deities and gods fall around you one by
Troop[122].pages[2].command[56].textData: one as men revolt against old world order.
Troop[122].pages[2].command[58].textData: However, your gospel back in the day was so strong that
Troop[122].pages[2].command[59].textData: people remember it loud and clear.
Troop[122].pages[2].command[61].textData: Your legacy had only grown stronger with you crushing the
Troop[122].pages[2].command[62].textData: warring kingdoms before the chaos began.
Troop[122].pages[2].command[66].textData: You are known as the fierce god and because there are no
Troop[122].pages[2].command[67].textData: other gods left to rival your power, you become the one and
Troop[122].pages[2].command[68].textData: only god despite your strength being limited to that of a
Troop[122].pages[2].command[74].textData: The harsh times breed harsh men. Mankind is physically in
Troop[122].pages[2].command[75].textData: its peak condition because of the warring tribes.
Troop[122].pages[2].command[77].textData: Because there is no centralized civilization, creating a
Troop[122].pages[2].command[78].textData: strong uniform religion proves out to be difficult.
Troop[122].pages[2].command[80].textData: With all new understanding of morals and customs, people
Troop[122].pages[2].command[81].textData: riot against the gods of older times.
Troop[122].pages[2].command[83].textData: You manage to withstand against the oncoming forces for
Troop[122].pages[2].command[84].textData: some time but eventually among mankind there appears a
Troop[122].pages[2].command[87].textData: You are beheaded and your mutilated torso is put on display.
Troop[122].pages[2].command[88].textData: You become a symbol of old and in this way you are remembered
Troop[122].pages[2].command[97].textData: Slowly in times of despair, people start to turn to your
Troop[122].pages[2].command[100].textDat: Many are killed and every new victim feeds the ongoing
Troop[122].pages[2].command[101].textDat: plague and destruction. This age would be known as the dark
Troop[122].pages[2].command[102].textDat: age in the history books, but your light would become an
Troop[122].pages[2].command[103].textDat: important factor in the survival of civilizations.
Troop[122].pages[2].command[105].textDat: You are known to men as the merciful god. New deities and
Troop[122].pages[2].command[106].textDat: false apostles rise as decades go by, but the foundation you
Troop[122].pages[2].command[107].textDat: laid during the dark age made you the pillar of morals for
Troop[122].pages[2].command[110].textDat: Even if your power is limited to that of the new gods, your
Troop[122].pages[2].command[111].textDat: legacy would eventually rival that of older gods...
Troop[122].pages[2].command[116].textDat: Sadly only few people find their way to your teachings
Troop[122].pages[2].command[117].textDat: because of your relatively less-known status.
Troop[122].pages[2].command[119].textDat: At best, you manage to form a cult around your religion. But
Troop[122].pages[2].command[120].textDat: because anyone who follows you is condemned as heretic in
Troop[122].pages[2].command[121].textDat: these times of great peril and prejudice, your followers
Troop[122].pages[2].command[122].textDat: resort to dark arts and dubious methods in order to survive.
Troop[122].pages[2].command[124].textDat: Centuries later you still manage to hang onto your cult
Troop[122].pages[2].command[125].textDat: status. However, generations of degenerative methods inside
Troop[122].pages[2].command[126].textDat: your cult has lead it becoming very notorious around modern
Troop[122].pages[2].command[129].textDat: You are considered far from the most notable gods and
Troop[122].pages[2].command[130].textDat: generally your followers are spit upon of the city streets.
Troop[122].pages[2].command[132].textDat: With your legacy dying, so does your strength. You are
Troop[122].pages[2].command[133].textDat: dethroned as time goes on by the new generation of new
Troop[122].pages[2].command[136].textDat: You are forgotten in the sands of time...

Troop[124].pages[2].command[44].textData: state of chaos. Common people got no one to turn onto and
Troop[124].pages[2].command[45].textData: thus they seek safety from smaller tribes and communes.

Troop[124].pages[2].command[52].textData: physical strength is the only thing that matters.

Troop[124].pages[2].command[56].textData: one as men revolt against old world order.
